result.name: kaplan-meier-survival-estimates-by-figo-stage-diagnosed-with-cervical-cancer
result.notes:
National Cancer Registration and Analysis Service (NCRAS). (2018). Cancer Registration: Kaplan-Meier survival estimates by FIGO stage for patients diagnosed with cervical cancer (ICD 10 C53) [Data set]. Public Health England. https://doi.org/10.25503/52jw-9g78

Kaplan-Meier survival estimates and confidence intervals (at 1, 2, 3, 4 and 5 years after diagnosis) for patients diagnosed with cervical cancer (ICD 10 C53),  between 01/01/2016 - 31/12/2016. The data is split into 5 cohorts; Groups 1, 2, 3 4 and 5 respectively. Each of these groups is defined below and survival estimates presented by FIGO stage.  Frequency counts are presented for total count of patients by group, by FIGO stage.

Group 1: Age >=20.0 to <24.5 and diagnosed between 1/1/2006 to 31/12/2016. 
Group 2: Age >=26.0 to <30.0 and diagnosed during 1/1/2006 - 31/8/2008;  Age >=26.0 to <28.0 diagnosed during 1/7/2009 - 31/12/2016;  Age >=28.0 to <29.0 diagnosed during 1/7/2009 - 31/12/2011; Age >=29.0 to <30.0 diagnosed during 1/7/2009 - 31/12/2016; Excluding Age >=26.0 to <30.0  and diagnosed during 1/9/2008 - 30/6/2009.
Group 3: Age >=24.5 to <25.0 and diagnosed during 1/1/2013 - 31/12/2016; Age >=25.0 to <25.5 and diagnosed during 1/1/2009 - 31/12/2016; Age >=25.5 to <26.0 and diagnosed during 1/1/2010 - 31/12/2015. 
Group 4: Age >=24.5 to <25.0 and diagnosed during 1/1/2006 - 31/12/2012; Age >=25.0 to <25.5 and diagnosed during 1/1/2006 - 31/12/2008; Age >=25.5 to <26.0and  diagnosed during 1/1/2006 -31/12/2009.
Group 5: Age >=28.0 to <29.0 and diagnosed during 1/1/2012 - 31/12/2016. 
Exclusions applied
** Cases with Figo Stage I where no additional stage information was available to allow classification to either Stage IA or Stage IB.
*** For cases with multiple cervical tumours survival time was calculated from the first diagnosis.
